  "title": "Source Format Reference Templates",
  "content": {
    "type": "factual",
    "format": "markdown",
    "body": "Different source formats use specific reference formats: Markdown/plain text uses `§<heading>` or `¶<paragraph_index>`; PDF/DOCX uses `page:<n>, para:<m>`; PPTX uses `slide:<n>`; video/audio uses `<HH:MM:SS>-<HH:MM:SS>`; web pages use `<section heading or XPath fragment>`."
